And here you see the way we define them.

00:06:53.359 --> 00:07:02.079
We give them a set of layers, and then we define a call method, and there we say how

00:07:02.079 --> 00:07:04.980
the layers should be chained one after the other.

00:07:04.980 --> 00:07:11.640
You can use that with static execution too, but it's really central in eager execution.

00:07:11.640 --> 00:07:16.619
We have it documented here, so you can click on that link and see how to use it.

00:07:16.619 --> 00:07:23.320
And now, when I do this, what I really can do is I can, like the drama which is actually

00:07:23.320 --> 00:07:26.600
going on, I can write my code like that.

00:07:26.600 --> 00:07:33.239
So first I have my generator, so the guy who's going to try to produce the fake images,

00:07:33.239 --> 00:07:35.799
and I define it as such a custom model.

00:07:35.799 --> 00:07:39.160
So I set it up.

00:07:39.160 --> 00:07:48.359
Then I go ahead and define my discriminator also as such a custom model, has its own logic.

00:07:48.359 --> 00:07:49.720
Nice.

00:07:49.720 --> 00:07:52.040
And then I go on.

00:07:52.040 --> 00:07:58.920
And now, again, in this antagonistic setting, both have different objectives.

00:07:58.920 --> 00:08:03.239
We always have this loss function in deep learning, and here each one has their own

00:08:03.239 --> 00:08:08.480
loss function, which you see is coded here.

00:08:08.480 --> 00:08:15.000
And after I did that, I can already start the action.

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:20.200
I'm going to iterate over the number of epochs, and then I'm going to iterate over the dataset,

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:26.000
so I always have these two nested loops, and then I execute the action, and when you

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:33.320
will look at code in this execution, it's always going to look like this, this way.

00:08:33.320 --> 00:08:34.320
So I'm iterating.

00:08:34.320 --> 00:08:40.679
Then I'm going to create this gradient tape, which is here recording what the actors are

00:08:40.679 --> 00:08:41.679
doing.

00:08:41.679 --> 00:08:47.640
I call the actors, let them do their action, I calculate their losses, and I'm going to

00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:48.640
do backprop.

00:08:49.080 --> 00:08:55.880
It's always such a loop like this, and it pretty much matches how we are picturing the

00:08:55.880 --> 00:08:58.760
action mentally.

00:08:58.760 --> 00:09:01.359
And what will happen if I do that?

